So how do you guarantee that the courier with the package will not flee?
Each user of the application together with the registration scans the ID card and indicates the bank account, payment or credit card.
These are the channels that give credibility to both the service and the person.
Couriers also collect stars based on sender ratings.
We also offer insurance, we still fine-tune the details.
The courier is liable for the uninsured consignment in the event of loss or damage, but does not assume responsibility for the content under the criminal law, if there is something illegal inside and does not know about it.
If the police stop him and find a machine gun or ten kilos of hash in his suitcase, criminal responsibility falls on the sender.
Is there a risk of misuse of sensitive data from the database?
If necessary, the registered are traceable by the administrative authority, which will be the only one who will have the opportunity to consult it, nor are we ourselves able to see them, the data are protected against misuse.
How much money will a courier receive after the successful delivery of the shipment?
The courier determines the price and gets the full amount he asks for.
The sender is charged several percent extra for mediating contact.
This money is our profit, but it's only a few percent because we want to push for volume.
No one can accuse the courier of not delivering the shipment when he actually delivered it, the receipt and delivery is verified using QR codes.
Are there any restrictions?
Whether in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can transport anything.
We have three sizes, small as a cube of butter, medium as a plate of eggs and the size of a bass of beer.
After that, there is no further restriction and if someone has a place in the car, they will transport the refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the app, so the courier can see what he's being asked to do.
You don’t even have to pack the thing if you don’t want to hide the content.
You put the forgotten sweatshirt in the courier's hand and that's it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to run the service?
A friend got the idea more than two years ago, I didn't pay much attention to it back then.
Then he showed me a demo application with a transnational reach, which mainly targets passengers by plane.
At that moment, I told him that I would not look for an investor, but I would like to become one myself and put savings into it.
The next year took development before we founded Shippansee LTD in London due to greater credibility of the entire product.
But this is not the version you are focusing on right now.
No, we focused on the Czech Republic, where we try to catch the application, because the whole thing had birth pains and there is still something to deal with and improve.
We try to respond to customer feedback and we do not deal with the foreign market so much at the moment.
We know it's a long run, but we're not rushing, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippansee LTD was the basic and most expensive application, the other two were upgrades in a way.
I will transfer it was created when we said that the national segment can be much more interesting and that we will at least learn it in the Czech Republic.
The third application of Mesík is local, for the city.
But it can send a package to the exact address and to the other end of the world.
It works for the sender just like I will take, but the difference is that as a courier you see shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator in your mobile.
The application for couriers who want to make a living from it, we called Mesík Profi.
So someone can make a profit by picking up packages around the city?
Exactly, the last application in Prague will be downloaded by a taxi driver, student, mother on parental leave, someone who wants to make the journey to work.
As everyone's fooling around with the Pokémon right now, they can collect this the same.
You can see where the orders are around the city, you come to it, you click and you see when it has to be delivered and you transfer the shipment.
It's set cheaper than competing services.
At the moment, we are still doing a web interface, which will be crucial for companies to send shipments, fill in data about them on the web, so it will create points on the map.
We are then able to invoice them every month to use the service.
Are you currently working on the project full-time?
It makes us busy, but we have it normally at work so that we can support the project and develop it.
There is no strong multinational investor behind us, we are two boys, one of whom had a brilliant idea and the other jumped into it with other suggestions and ideas.
Now we are looking for an investor strong enough to manage not the Czech market with us, but who should, with the pardon of the ball, go with us to the global product and become another huge player in the market like AirBnB and Uber.
